# System Workflow

The Smart Road Assist system simulates a roadside assistance platform
where users can request help and dispatchers assign mechanics.

1. Registration and login

All users register through the Dispatcher.
Dispatcher stores authentication data in MongoDB.

Each user has a role:

ADMIN
USER
MECHANIC
DISPATCHER

Dispatcher validates tokens and permissions for every request.

2. Creating a request

A USER sends a request for help.

POST /requests

The request contains:

type
description
location

Request status is set to CREATED.

3. Dispatcher assigns mechanic

A DISPATCHER checks open requests.

GET /requests

Dispatcher selects a mechanic and assigns the request.

PUT /requests/{id}/assign

Request status becomes ASSIGNED.

Mechanic status becomes BUSY.

4. Mechanic processes request

Mechanic updates request status.

PUT /requests/{id}/status

Possible values:

IN_PROGRESS
DONE

5. Payment

After request is done,
payment service creates payment.

POST /payments

Status:

PENDING
PAID
FAILED

6. Notification

Notification service sends message to user.

POST /notifications

Example messages:

Mechanic assigned
Request completed
Payment received

7. Dispatcher responsibilities

Dispatcher is the single entry point.

It performs:

authentication
authorization
routing
logging
error handling

All services are accessed through dispatcher.

8. RMM Level 3

Each entity is a resource:

users
requests
mechanics
payments
notifications

Each resource has its own URI.

Correct HTTP methods are used.

Responses may contain links to related resources.
